The experiments were conducted in a cryostat connected to a cryogenerator with a base temperature of 10 K. The experimental cell, a closed metallic box placed in a vacuum, is thermally connected to the cold stage of the cryogenerator via thermal impedance. Temperature control within the cell is achieved using a PID LakeShore 331 controller, which regulates the heating power passing through the thermal impedance. Inside the cell are two independent plane capacitors with equal surface areas but differing thicknesses, labeled as thick (
L_{thick}
) and thin (
L_{thin}
